<!--
    PUF France Use Case 26: Invoice with Contractual Reservation Clause (Retenue de Garantie)

    Business Scenario:
    - Construction company (SELLER) invoices for building renovation services
    - A 5% retention guarantee (retenue de garantie) applies per contract
    - Invoice is issued for the FULL amount (100%) - retention is a payment timing arrangement
    - BUYER pays 95% immediately; 5% withheld pending satisfactory completion
    - The retention amount is expressed ONLY as free-text note (BT-21=ABU / BT-22)

    Key UC26 Concepts:
    - EN 16931 and EXTENDED-CTC-FR do NOT support structured payment schedules
      with a reservation-conditioned amount
    - Retention can ONLY be expressed via BT-21 = ABU (Contract clause) + BT-22 text
    - BT-115 (Amount due) = full amount (100%), NOT the 95% immediate portion

    VAT Treatment (This example: Services, VAT on cash basis):
    - VAT is due only on amounts actually received
    - SELLER transmits "Encaissée" lifecycle status for each payment:
      * First "Encaissée" at 95% upon initial partial payment
      * Second "Encaissée" at 5% if reservation is lifted
    - If reservation is enforced → SELLER must issue credit note (see companion example)
    - No "Encaissée" status needed for the credit note

    Alternative VAT scenario (VAT on debits):
    - Full VAT at invoice issuance regardless of retention
    - No "Encaissée" lifecycle management needed
    - If retention enforced → credit note still required

    Worked Example:
    - Total HT (BT-109): 40,000.00 EUR
    - Total VAT (BT-110) @ 20%: 8,000.00 EUR
    - Total TTC (BT-112): 48,000.00 EUR
    - Amount Due (BT-115): 48,000.00 EUR (full amount)
    - Immediate payment: 45,600.00 EUR (95%)
    - Withheld retention: 2,400.00 EUR (5%)

    Source: XP Z12-014 Annexe A v1.3, Section 3.2.25
-->
<Invoice xmlns="urn:pagero:PageroUniversalFormat:Invoice:1.0" xmlns:cac="urn:pagero:CommonAggregateComponents:1.0" xmlns:cbc="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonBasicComponents-2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:puf="urn:pagero:ExtensionComponent:1.0" xmlns:ext="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonExtensionComponents-2">

    <!-- BT-24 Specification identifier -->
    <cbc:CustomizationID>urn:pagero.com:puf:billing:2.0</cbc:CustomizationID>
